---
title: Chicken Sausage Pizzas with Broiled Zucchini and Fresh Oregano
description: Put down the phone for delivery: this dinner is all about creating a masterful flatbread on your own terms. You’ll practice topping the base with layers of tomato sauce, cheese, and sausage. And because a little bit of green is always a plus, there are slices of zucchini and some fresh oregano, too. All these ingredients work together to deliver a baked masterpiece that will keep you by the oven door, anticipating the moment of peak meltiness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5bb4dd3cae08b5077c528a82-48176012.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-sausage-flatbreads-5bb4dd3cae08b5077c528a82-7ee8b973.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-pizzas-5bb4dd3cae08b5077c528a82
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2150 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Slice
@zucchini{1} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Pick @oregano{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems;
discard stems. Roughly chop leaves.

Place zucchini on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{},
and ½ tsp @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (we'll use more later). Place under broiler and
broil until softened and browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove baking sheet from broiler,
then adjust oven temperature to 450 degrees.

> TIP: Keep an eye on the zucchini—it can burn.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{3%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
@Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} to pan along with half the oregano,
breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, tossing, until browned and no longer pink,
~{4-6%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Place @flatbreads{2} on another lightly oiled baking sheet. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Spread a thin layer of @crushed tomatoes{6.88%ounce} across the
tops of the flatbreads (we used half the box). Sprinkle with salt, pepper,
and ½ tsp Italian seasoning (you'll have some left over). Scatter sausage and
zucchini over evenly, then follow with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake flatbreads in oven until golden brown at the edges and cheese melts,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Scatter remaining oregano over flatbreads (to taste), then cut into slices and
serve.